==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ensphere
<hw>En*sphere"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>en-</ets> + <ets>sphere</ets>. Cf. <er>Insphere</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To place in a sphere; to envelop.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His ample shoulders in a cloud <qex>ensphered</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Chapman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To form into a sphere.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Enstamp</ent>⟦br⟧
